values.help: Sets the minimum off time before another heating/cooling cycle can begin to provide compressor short cycle protection.  The thermostat screen will display WAIT when minimum off time is being enforced.
values.label: Minimum Off Time

values.help: Sets the minimum run time before a heating/cooling cycle can turn off to prevent rapid cycling.  Thermostat screen will display "Cool ON" or "Heat ON" while the minimum run time is being enforced.
values.label: Minimum Run Time

values.help: Sets the delta from setpoint that stage 1 heating starts.
values.label: Heating Delta Stage 1 ON

values.help: Sets the delta from setpoint that stage 1 heating stops. Stage 1 turns off at setpoint minus (-) Delta Stage 1.
values.label: Heating Delta Stage 1 OFF

values.help: Sets the delta from setpoint that stage 2 heating starts.
values.label: Heating Delta Stage 2 ON

values.help: Sets the delta from setpoint that stage 2 heating stops. Stage 1 turns off at setpoint minus (-) Delta Stage 2.
values.label: Heating Delta Stage 2 OFF

values.help: Sets the delta from setpoint that stage 3 heating starts.
values.label: Heating Delta Stage 3 ON

values.help: Sets the delta from setpoint that stage 3 heating stops. Stage 1 turns off at setpoint minus (-) Delta Stage 3.
values.label: Heating Delta Stage 3 OFF

values.help: Sets the delta from setpoint that stage 1 cooling starts.
values.label: Cooling Delta Stage 1 ON

values.help: Sets the delta from setpoint that stage 1 cooling stops. Stage 1 turns off at setpoint minus (-) Delta Stage 1.
values.label: Cooling Delta Stage 1 OFF

values.help: Sets the delta from setpoint that stage 2 cooling starts.
values.label: Cooling Delta Stage 2 ON

values.help: Sets the delta from setpoint that stage 2 cooling stops. Stage 1 turns off at setpoint minus (-) Delta Stage 2.
values.label: Cooling Delta Stage 2 OFF

values.help: Sets the minimum separation between the heating and cooling setpoints.  Attempts to lower the cooling below the heating setpoint by this amount will PUSH the heating setpoint down to maintain this separation. Same for setting the heating setpoint above the cooling setpoint, it will PUSH the cooling setpoint up to maintain this separation. Settings in F.
values.label: H/C Delta

values.help: Energy Saving Mode (ESM) Setpoints are the setpoints used when the Energy Saving Mode schedule is selected in the Schedule Mode screen (or via Z-Wave control). Setting in F.
values.label: ESM Setpoint--Heating

values.help: Energy Saving Mode (ESM) Setpoints are the setpoints used when the Energy Saving Mode schedule is selected in the Schedule Mode screen (or via Z-Wave control).
values.label: ESM Setpoint--Cooling

values.help: The fan cycler function cycles the HVAC system fan for an ON period followed by an OFF period continuously. Used to provide minimum air ventilation requirements. When the Fan ON time is set to a value greater than 0, an additional Cycler Fan mode is present when pressing the FAN button on the thermostat.
values.label: Fan ON Time

values.help: The fan cycler function cycles the HVAC system fan for an ON period followed by an OFF period continuously. Used to provide minimum air ventilation requirements. When the Fan ON time is set to a value greater than 0, an additional Cycler Fan mode is present when pressing the FAN button on the thermostat.
values.label: Fan OFF Time

values.help: 0 = no aux heat, 1 = aux heat enabled.
values.label: Aux Heat Enable

values.help: Set to 1 if running schedule (RUN is displayed on the thermostat screen).
values.label: Run Schedule

values.help:
Heating 1 Setpoint (does this vary with ESM, etc. or is this for the "Hold" setting?
	      Default:
	      HOLD   55F / 13C
	      RUN    60F / xxC
	      ESM    64F / xxC (unless parameter xx has been changed)
values.label: Heating 1 Setpoint

values.help:
Backlight Timeout is the time (in seconds) from the last 
	      button press to the backlight going out.  The time-out
	      can be set between 0 and 120
	      seconds.  When set to 0, the backlight will remain
	      always on.
	      Default:  30
values.label: Backlight Timeout

values.help:
Sets the maximum heating setpoint value.  Will not ramp
	      or accept setpoints higher than this maximum.
	      Minimum:  55F / xxC
	      Maximum:  90F / xxC
	      Default:  90F / 32C
values.label: Max Heat Setpoint

values.help:
Sets the minimum cooling setpoint value.  Will not ramp
	      or accept setpoints lower than this minimum.
	      Minimum:  60F / xxC
	      Maximum:  99F / xxC
	      Default:  60F / 15C
values.label: Min Cool Setpoint

values.help:
This is the time before any screen reverts to the Minimized
	      Screen (temperature display only), after you stop pushing
	      buttons.  Minimized Screen feature is disabled by setting this
	      time to 0. 
	      Default:  0
values.label: Screen Timeout

values.help:
The internal temperature sensor can be calibrated to report
	      values different from its actual reading.  The offset can
	      range from -7 degrees to +7 degrees.
	      Default:  0
values.label: Sensor (Internal) Offset

values.help:
The Screen Contrast sets the contrast level of the LCD display.
	      The contrast can be set between 0 and 20.  If the display 
	      is too light, use a higher number.  If dark lines appear on 
	      the screen, use a lower number.
	      Default:  10
values.label: Screen Contrast

values.help:
When enabled (set to 1), the local thermostat's scheduler 
	      function is enabled.
	      Default:  0
values.label: Schedule Enable

values.help:
This value holds information about the first schedule
	      setpoints for Sundays.
	      
	      Byte 1: Hour   (0-23)
	      Byte 2: Minute (0-59)
	      Byte 3: Heat Setpoint (degrees)
	      Byte 4: Cool Setpoint (degrees)
	      
	      Default:  0x06004643 06:00AM 70F / 67F
	      0x06001519 06:00AM 21C / 25C
values.label: Schedule Sun-1
